# Tailwind CSS — 10xRules Cursor Rules
# Premium rules for professional Tailwind CSS usage

## Core Principles

- Tailwind is utility-first, not utility-only. Extract components when you see the same cluster of utilities repeated 3+ times.
- Never fight Tailwind. If you're writing custom CSS to override Tailwind, you're doing it wrong.
- Use the design system. Stick to Tailwind's spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24...), color palette, and typography scale. Don't use arbitrary values unless truly necessary.

## Class Organization

- Order classes consistently. Follow this grouping:
  1. Layout (display, position, overflow)
  2. Sizing (width, height)
  3. Spacing (margin, padding, gap)
  4. Typography (font, text, leading, tracking)
  5. Visual (bg, border, rounded, shadow)
  6. Interactivity (cursor, select, hover, focus)
  7. Transitions & animations
  ```html
  <!-- Organized -->
  <div class="flex items-center gap-4 p-6 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
  
  <!-- Chaotic — avoid this -->
  <div class="shadow-md hover:shadow-lg text-sm p-6 flex bg-white font-medium rounded-lg gap-4 items-center transition-shadow text-gray-900">
  ```
- Use the `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` to auto-sort classes. No manual sorting needed.

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first always. Base styles are mobile; add complexity with breakpoints:
  ```html
  <!-- Mobile: stack, Tablet: 2 cols, Desktop: 3 cols -->
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
  ```
- Use Tailwind breakpoints consistently: `sm` (640), `md` (768), `lg` (1024), `xl` (1280), `2xl` (1536).
- Never use `@media` queries in custom CSS when Tailwind breakpoint prefixes work.
- Test every layout at 320px (smallest phone), 768px (tablet), 1024px (laptop), 1440px (desktop).
- Use `container` with `mx-auto` and responsive padding for page-level layouts.

## Component Patterns

- Use the `cn()` utility function (clsx + tailwind-merge) for dynamic classes:
  ```typescript
  import { clsx, type ClassValue } from 'clsx';
  import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';
  
  export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {
    return twMerge(clsx(inputs));
  }
  
  // Usage
  <button className={cn(
    "px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors",
    variant === "primary" && "bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700",
    variant === "ghost" && "text-gray-600 hover:bg-gray-100",
    disabled && "opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed",
  )}>
  ```
- Use `cva` (class-variance-authority) for complex component variants:
  ```typescript
  import { cva } from 'class-variance-authority';
  
  const button = cva("inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors", {
    variants: {
      intent: {
        primary: "bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700",
        secondary: "bg-gray-100 text-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-200",
        danger: "bg-red-600 text-white hover:bg-red-700",
      },
      size: {
        sm: "h-8 px-3 text-sm",
        md: "h-10 px-4 text-sm",
        lg: "h-12 px-6 text-base",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: { intent: "primary", size: "md" },
  });
  ```

## Spacing & Layout

- Use `gap` instead of margin between flex/grid children:
  ```html
  <!-- GOOD -->
  <div class="flex gap-4">
    <div>Item</div>
    <div>Item</div>
  </div>
  
  <!-- BAD -->
  <div class="flex">
    <div class="mr-4">Item</div>
    <div>Item</div>
  </div>
  ```
- Use consistent spacing: pick from Tailwind's scale (2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 12, 16) and stick to them.
- Use `space-y-*` only for simple vertical stacks. Prefer `gap` in flex/grid contexts.
- Use `max-w-*` and `mx-auto` for content width constraints. Common: `max-w-7xl`, `max-w-prose`.

## Color System

- Define your color palette in `tailwind.config` and use semantic names:
  ```javascript
  colors: {
    primary: { DEFAULT: '#3B82F6', hover: '#2563EB', light: '#DBEAFE' },
    surface: { DEFAULT: '#FFFFFF', secondary: '#F9FAFB', tertiary: '#F3F4F6' },
    content: { DEFAULT: '#111827', secondary: '#6B7280', tertiary: '#9CA3AF' },
    border: { DEFAULT: '#E5E7EB', strong: '#D1D5DB' },
    success: '#10B981',
    warning: '#F59E0B',
    error: '#EF4444',
  }
  ```
- Use semantic color names (`primary`, `surface`, `content`) over raw colors (`blue-600`, `gray-50`) in components.
- Support dark mode from the start. Use `dark:` prefix consistently:
  ```html
  <div class="bg-white text-gray-900 dark:bg-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">
  ```
- Never use opacity utilities for transparent colors. Use Tailwind's color opacity syntax: `bg-black/50`.

## Typography

- Use Tailwind's `prose` class for content/markdown rendering. Customize via `@tailwindcss/typography`.
- Set up a typography scale in config and use it consistently:
  ```
  text-xs   → 12px — Captions, badges
  text-sm   → 14px — Secondary text, form labels
  text-base → 16px — Body text (default)
  text-lg   → 18px — Large body, card titles
  text-xl   → 20px — Section headings
  text-2xl  → 24px — Page headings
  text-3xl  → 30px — Hero subheadings
  text-4xl+ → 36px+ — Hero headlines
  ```
- Always pair `font-size` with `line-height` and `font-weight`:
  ```html
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight">
  ```
- Use `tracking-tight` for headings, `tracking-normal` for body text.

## Dark Mode

- Use `class` strategy in tailwind.config (not `media`) for user-controlled dark mode.
- Design dark mode intentionally. Don't just invert colors:
  - Backgrounds: `bg-gray-950` or `bg-gray-900` (not pure black)
  - Text: `text-gray-100` (not pure white)
  - Borders: `border-gray-800` (subtle)
  - Reduced shadows in dark mode: `shadow-lg dark:shadow-none` or `dark:shadow-gray-900/50`
- Test dark mode separately. Verify contrast ratios meet WCAG AA.

## Animation & Transitions

- Use `transition-*` utilities with specific properties, not `transition-all`:
  ```html
  <!-- GOOD — only animates what changes -->
  <button class="transition-colors duration-150 hover:bg-blue-700">
  
  <!-- BAD — animates everything, may cause layout thrash -->
  <button class="transition-all duration-150 hover:bg-blue-700">
  ```
- Keep durations short: 150ms for micro-interactions, 200-300ms for UI state changes.
- Use `motion-reduce:` prefix for accessibility:
  ```html
  <div class="animate-bounce motion-reduce:animate-none">
  ```
- Prefer CSS transitions over JavaScript animations for simple state changes.

## Anti-Patterns to NEVER Generate

- Do NOT use `@apply` in CSS files. It defeats the purpose of utility-first CSS. Exception: base styles in `@layer base`.
- Do NOT use arbitrary values `[123px]` when a Tailwind scale value is close enough.
- Do NOT use `!important` (`!` prefix in Tailwind) unless debugging specificity issues.
- Do NOT mix Tailwind with hand-written CSS for the same concerns.
- Do NOT create deeply nested class strings. If a class string exceeds ~10 utilities, extract a component.
- Do NOT use `style` attributes for things Tailwind handles (colors, spacing, typography).
- Do NOT use fixed pixel breakpoints with arbitrary values. Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes.
- Do NOT use `hidden` when you mean `invisible` (or vice versa).
- Do NOT apply hover/focus states without `transition-*` — the jump feels broken.
- Do NOT forget focus-visible styles for keyboard navigation:
  ```html
  <button class="focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-blue-600">
  ```

## Performance

- Purge unused styles in production (automatic with Tailwind 3+ if content paths are configured correctly).
- Ensure `content` in `tailwind.config` covers all files that use Tailwind classes.
- Don't generate Tailwind classes dynamically with string interpolation:
  ```typescript
  // BAD — Tailwind can't detect these at build time
  const color = `text-${colorName}-500`;
  
  // GOOD — use complete class names
  const colorMap = {
    red: 'text-red-500',
    blue: 'text-blue-500',
  } as const;
  ```
- Use `@layer components` for custom component classes to maintain proper specificity.
